        "thinking": "Now I have a full picture. Let me replace everything from the banner styles to the banner script with the new light design.\n\nThe key changes:\n1. New CSS: glassmorphism, white/light palette, pure CSS hover opening\n2. New HTML: centered single line \"▸ Analyze with AI\", simpler structure\n3. New JS: only for language switch + copy (no click toggle needed)\n4. Adjacent sibling `#banner-spacer` for content shift on hover\n\nFor the hover-based spacer trick:\n```css\n#banner-spacer { height: 42px; transition: height 0.25s cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1); }\n\n\n#recruiter-banner:hover + #banner-spacer { height: calc(42px + 33vh); }\n```\n\nBut I'm realizing a UX problem with pure CSS hover—if the user moves their mouse away from the banner while trying to click the language buttons or copy button, the banner will collapse since they're no longer hovering. I need to think through whether the spacer approach with `padding-top: 20px` on the body is the right move here, or if I should keep some JavaScript to manage the open state more reliably.\n\nActually, since the buttons are inside the banner itself, hovering over them keeps the panel open, so this should work fine. Let me design the visual hierarchy: a minimal 40px strip with white frosted glass, centered text saying \"▸ Analyze with AI\" in a subtle indigo tone, and a rotating chevron on the right. The panel below should have the same frosted aesthetic with soft shadows, minimal language pills in slate, an outlined copy button, and a light background for the prompt area.\n\nFor spacing, I need a 40px spacer normally, but when the panel hovers it expands to 40px plus the panel height.\n\nWriting the CSS styles... Still writing styles... Still writing styles... Still writing styles... Writing the JavaScript initialization... Finishing the copy function and then reconsidering the body padding since the spacer is now the first child—I need to think through how the spacing will work with the 20px padding already on the body.\n\nI'll make the edits in one clean pass, replacing the style block, body tag, and banner section together.",
